Segun Adewole The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), has received the Governor of Plateau State, Simon Lalong, at the State House in Abuja on Friday. This was disclosed by his Personal Assistant on Broadcast Media, Buhari Sallau who shared photos from the meeting. “President @MBuhari receives in audience Plateau State Governor H.E. Simon Lalong in State House on 29th Jan 2021,” Sallau wrote on Twitter without other details about the meeting. READ ALSO: Seven repentant bandits surrender weapons in Zamfara The PUNCH had earlier reported that Lalong who is the Chairman of the Northern Governors’ Forum revealed that the 19 Northern States Governors have agreed to take the first doses of the COVID-19 vaccine when they arrive in the country. He said this while discussing the safety and efficacy of the vaccines at a webinar organised by the Sir Ahmadu Bello Memorial Foundation. READ ALSO: Service chiefs: Buhari made informed decision, says ex-Borno gov, Shettima 